	"html": "<a id=\"t.3eaf70e849ae48eae03544bd83f8452851f70638\"></a><a id=\"t.0\"></a><div class=\"stickers\"></div><h2 class=\"c14 c21\" id=\"h.5vk9s4eovuiz\"><span class=\"c28\">Summary</span></h2><p class=\"c14\"><span class=\"c8\">In this Dokidoki Alert, IORG presents 8 information manipulation narratives with CCP participation between April 1<sup>st</sup> and November 21<sup>st</sup>, 2021. These narratives might affect public opinion and vote on the referendums on December 18<sup>th</sup>, 2021. In addition, 2 government narratives are also presented here due to oversimplification and unfalsifiability in both supporting and opposing statements. IORG argues that these narratives are not conducive to the public discourse, risk being used to further mislead and widen existing divides, and hinder the reinforcement of Taiwan’s democracy.</span></p><p class=\"c14\"><span class=\"c8\">In the lead up to the referendums, IORG will publish one Dokidoki Alert each week for 3 consecutive weeks, exposing information manipulation with data science and provide evidence to CCP involvement. We hope this would help you, Taiwan’s voters, to cast your most informed vote on December 18<sup>th</sup>.</span></p><a id=\"t.a5e069f7ca59acd11b6613c02772a74e58363288\"></a><a id=\"t.1\"></a><div class=\"gdoc-table-container\"><div class=\"table\"><table class=\"c23\"><tbody><tr class=\"c9\"><th class=\"c11 c22 w-min-12\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c13\"><span class=\"c2\">Narratives</span></p></th><th class=\"c11 c22 w-min-12\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c13\"><span class=\"c2\">Features</span></p></th><th class=\"c11 c22 list-set bubbles w-min-16 ccp china other\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c13\"><span class=\"c2\">Nodes</span></p><ul class=\"c7 lst-kix_76scn0kj0h56-0 start\"><li class=\"c6 li-bullet-0 ccp\"><span class=\"c2\">CCP</span></li><li class=\"c6 li-bullet-0 china\"><span class=\"c2\">China</span></li><li class=\"c6 li-bullet-0 other\"><span c